  38 bool IsAlwaysTrue(Node* node, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit, ContainerScope* containerScope)
  39 {
  40     std::unique_ptr<Value> value = Evaluate(node, boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetTypeByName(U"bool"), containerScope, boundCompileUnit, true, nullptr, node->GetSpan());
  41     if (value)
  42     {
  43         if (value->GetValueType() == ValueType::boolValue)
  44         {
  45             BoolValue* boolValue = static_cast<BoolValue*>(value.get());
  46             return boolValue->GetValue() == true;
  47         }
  48     }
  49     return false;
  50 }
  51 
  52 bool TerminatesFunction(StatementNode* statement, bool inForEverLoop, ContainerScope* containerScope, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit)
  53 {
  54     switch (statement->GetNodeType())
  55     {
  56         case NodeType::compoundStatementNode:
  57         {
  58             CompoundStatementNode* compoundStatement = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(statement);
  59             int n = compoundStatement->Statements().Count();
  60             for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
  61             {
  62                 StatementNode* statement = compoundStatement->Statements()[i];
  63                 if (TerminatesFunction(statement, inForEverLoop, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
  64             }
  65             break;
  66         }
  67         case NodeType::ifStatementNode:
  68         {
  69             IfStatementNode* ifStatement = static_cast<IfStatementNode*>(statement);
  70             if (inForEverLoop || ifStatement->ElseS())
  71             {
  72                 if (TerminatesFunction(ifStatement->ThenS(), inForEverLoop, containerScope, boundCompileUnit) && 
  73                     inForEverLoop || (ifStatement->ElseS() && TerminatesFunction(ifStatement->ElseS(), inForEverLoop, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)))
  74                 {
  75                     return true;
  76                 }
  77             }
  78             break;
  79         }
  80         case NodeType::whileStatementNode:
  81         {
  82             WhileStatementNode* whileStatement = static_cast<WhileStatementNode*>(statement);
  83             if (IsAlwaysTrue(whileStatement->Condition(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope))
  84             {
  85                 if (TerminatesFunction(whileStatement->Statement(), true, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
  86             }
  87             break;
  88         }
  89         case NodeType::doStatementNode:
  90         {
  91             DoStatementNode* doStatement = static_cast<DoStatementNode*>(statement);
  92             if (IsAlwaysTrue(doStatement->Condition(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope))
  93             {
  94                 if (TerminatesFunction(doStatement->Statement(), true, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
  95             }
  96             break;
  97         }
  98         case NodeType::forStatementNode:
  99         {
 100             ForStatementNode* forStatement = static_cast<ForStatementNode*>(statement);
 101             if (!forStatement->Condition() || IsAlwaysTrue(forStatement->Condition(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope))
 102             {
 103                 if (TerminatesFunction(forStatement->ActionS(), true, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
 104             }
 105             break;
 106         }
 107         default:
 108         {
 109             if (statement->IsFunctionTerminatingNode())
 110             {
 111                 return true;
 112             }
 113             break;
 114         }
 115     }
 116     return false;
 117 }
 118 
 119 bool TerminatesCase(StatementNode* statementNode)
 120 {
 121     if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::ifStatementNode)
 122     {
 123         IfStatementNode* ifStatementNode = static_cast<IfStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 124         if (ifStatementNode->ElseS())
 125         {
 126             if (TerminatesCase(ifStatementNode->ThenS()) && TerminatesCase(ifStatementNode->ElseS()))
 127             {
 128                 return true;
 129             }
 130         }
 131     }
 132     else if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
 133     {
 134         CompoundStatementNode* compoundStatement = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 135         int n = compoundStatement->Statements().Count();
 136         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 137         {
 138             StatementNode* statementNode = compoundStatement->Statements()[i];
 139             if (TerminatesCase(statementNode))
 140             {
 141                 return true;
 142             }
 143         }
 144     }
 145     else
 146     {
 147         return statementNode->IsCaseTerminatingNode();
 148     }
 149     return false;
 150 }
 151 
 152 bool TerminatesDefault(StatementNode* statementNode)
 153 {
 154     if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::ifStatementNode)
 155     {
 156         IfStatementNode* ifStatementNode = static_cast<IfStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 157         if (ifStatementNode->ElseS())
 158         {
 159             if (TerminatesDefault(ifStatementNode->ThenS()) && TerminatesDefault(ifStatementNode->ElseS()))
 160             {
 161                 return true;
 162             }
 163         }
 164     }
 165     else if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
 166     {
 167         CompoundStatementNode* compoundStatement = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 168         int n = compoundStatement->Statements().Count();
 169         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 170         {
 171             StatementNode* statementNode = compoundStatement->Statements()[i];
 172             if (TerminatesDefault(statementNode))
 173             {
 174                 return true;
 175             }
 176         }
 177     }
 178     else
 179     {
 180         return statementNode->IsDefaultTerminatingNode();
 181     }
 182     return false;
 183 }

 187 void CheckFunctionReturnPaths(FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol, FunctionNode& functionNode, ContainerScope* containerScope, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit)
 188 {
 189     CheckFunctionReturnPaths(functionSymbol, functionNode.Body(), functionNode.GetSpan(), containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 190 }
 191 
 192 void CheckFunctionReturnPaths(FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol, CompoundStatementNode* bodyNode, const Span& span, ContainerScope* containerScope, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit)
 193 {
 194     TypeSymbol* returnType = functionSymbol->ReturnType();
 195     if (!returnType || returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::voidTypeSymbol) return;
 196     if (functionSymbol->IsExternal()) return;
 197     if (functionSymbol->IsAbstract()) return;
 198     CompoundStatementNode* body = bodyNode;
 199     if (body)
 200     {
 201         int n = body->Statements().Count();
 202         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 203         {
 204             StatementNode* statement = body->Statements()[i];
 205             if (TerminatesFunction(statement, false, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return;
 206         }
 207         throw Exception(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule(), "not all control paths terminate in return or throw statement", span);
 208     }
 209 }

 212     boundCompileUnit(boundCompileUnit_), symbolTable(boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable()), module(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule()), containerScope(nullptr), statement(), compoundLevel(0), insideCatch(false), 
 213     currentClass(nullptr), currentFunction(nullptr), currentStaticConstructorSymbol(nullptr), currentStaticConstructorNode(nullptr), currentConstructorSymbol(nullptr), 
 214     currentConstructorNode(nullptr), currentDestructorSymbol(nullptr), currentDestructorNode(nullptr), currentMemberFunctionSymbol(nullptr), currentMemberFunctionNode(nullptr), 
 215     switchConditionType(nullptr), currentCaseValueMap(nullptr), currentGotoCaseStatements(nullptr), currentGotoDefaultStatements(nullptr), postfix(false), compilingThrow(false), 
 216     compilingReleaseExceptionStatement(false), dontCheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols(false)
 217 {
 218 }

 220 void StatementBinder::Visit(CompileUnitNode& compileUnitNode)
 221 {
 222     if (compileUnitNode.IsSynthesizedUnit())
 223     {
 224         dontCheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols = true;
 225     }
 226     compileUnitNode.GlobalNs()->Accept(*this);
 227     dontCheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols = false;
 228     Symbol* symbol = symbolTable.GlobalNs().GetContainerScope()->Lookup(U"System.Runtime.AddCompileUnitFunction");
 229     if (symbol)
 230     {
 231         if (symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::functionGroupSymbol)
 232         {
 233             FunctionGroupSymbol* functionGroup = static_cast<FunctionGroupSymbol*>(symbol);
 234             FunctionSymbol* systemRuntimeAddCompileUnitFunctionSymbol = functionGroup->GetFunction();
 235             boundCompileUnit.SetSystemRuntimeAddCompileUnitFunctionSymbol(systemRuntimeAddCompileUnitFunctionSymbol);
 236         }
 237     }
 238     FunctionSymbol* initCompileUnitSymbol = boundCompileUnit.GetInitCompileUnitFunctionSymbol();
 239     if (initCompileUnitSymbol == nullptr)
 240     {
 241         boundCompileUnit.GenerateCompileUnitInitialization();
 242     }
 243 }

 245 struct NamespaceVisitor 
 246 {
 247     NamespaceVisitor(BoundCompileUnit* cu_, BoundNamespace* ns_) : cu(cu_), ns(ns_)
 248     {
 249         cu->PushNamespace(ns);
 250     }
 251     ~NamespaceVisitor()
 252     {
 253         cu->PopNamespace();
 254     }
 255     BoundCompileUnit* cu;
 256     BoundNamespace* ns;
 257 };
 258 
 259 void StatementBinder::Visit(NamespaceNode& namespaceNode)
 260 {
 261     std::unique_ptr<BoundNamespace> ns(new BoundNamespace(module, namespaceNode));
 262     boundCompileUnit.PushNamespace(ns.get());
 263     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 264     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&namespaceNode);
 265     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 266     int n = namespaceNode.Members().Count();
 267     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 268     {
 269         Node* member = namespaceNode.Members()[i];
 270         member->Accept(*this);
 271     }
 272     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 273     boundCompileUnit.PopNamespace();
 274     boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::unique_ptr<BoundNode>(ns.release()));
 275 }

 277 void StatementBinder::Visit(EnumTypeNode& enumTypeNode)

 282     std::unique_ptr<BoundEnumTypeDefinition> boundEnum(new BoundEnumTypeDefinition(module, enumTypeSymbol));
 283     boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundEnum));
 284 }

 286 void StatementBinder::Visit(ClassNode& classNode)
 287 {
 288     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 289     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&classNode);
 290     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTypeSymbol || symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTemplateSpecializationSymbol, "class type symbol expected");
 291     ClassTypeSymbol* classTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 292     if (classTypeSymbol->IsClassTemplate())
 293     {
 294         return;
 295     }
 296     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 297     std::unique_ptr<BoundClass> boundClass(new BoundClass(module, classTypeSymbol));
 298     BoundClass* prevClass = currentClass;
 299     currentClass = boundClass.get();
 300     int n = classNode.Members().Count();
 301     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 302     {
 303         Node* classMember = classNode.Members()[i];
 304         classMember->Accept(*this);
 305     }
 306     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(classNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 307     boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundClass));
 308     DestructorSymbol* destructorSymbol = classTypeSymbol->Destructor();
 309     if (destructorSymbol && destructorSymbol->IsGeneratedFunction() && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::info))
 310     {
 311         if (!boundCompileUnit.IsGeneratedDestructorInstantiated(destructorSymbol))
 312         {
 313             boundCompileUnit.SetGeneratedDestructorInstantiated(destructorSymbol);
 314             GenerateDestructorImplementation(currentClass, destructorSymbol, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, currentFunction, classNode.GetSpan());
 315         }
 316     }
 317     currentClass = prevClass;
 318     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 319 }

 321 void StatementBinder::Visit(MemberVariableNode& memberVariableNode)
 322 {
 323     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&memberVariableNode);
 324     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::memberVariableSymbol, "member variable symbol expected");
 325     MemberVariableSymbol* memberVariableSymbol = static_cast<MemberVariableSymbol*>(symbol);
 326     TypeSymbol* typeSymbol = memberVariableSymbol->GetType();
 327     if (typeSymbol->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 328     {
 329         ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(typeSymbol);
 330         DestructorSymbol* destructorSymbol = classType->Destructor();
 331         if (destructorSymbol && destructorSymbol->IsGeneratedFunction() && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::info))
 332         {
 333             if (!boundCompileUnit.IsGeneratedDestructorInstantiated(destructorSymbol))
 334             {
 335                 boundCompileUnit.SetGeneratedDestructorInstantiated(destructorSymbol);
 336                 std::unique_ptr<BoundClass> boundClass(new BoundClass(module, classType));
 337                 GenerateDestructorImplementation(boundClass.get(), destructorSymbol, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, currentFunction, memberVariableNode.GetSpan());
 338                 boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundClass));
 339             }
 340         }
 341     }
 342 }

 344 void StatementBinder::Visit(FunctionNode& functionNode)
 345 {
 346     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 347     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&functionNode);
 348     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::functionSymbol, "function symbol expected");
 349     FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol = static_cast<FunctionSymbol*>(symbol);
 350     if (!dontCheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols)
 351     {
 352         functionSymbol->FunctionGroup()->CheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols();
 353     }
 354     if (functionSymbol->IsFunctionTemplate())
 355     {
 356         return;
 357     }
 358     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 359     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(&boundCompileUnit, functionSymbol));
 360     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 361     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 362     if (functionNode.Body())
 363     {
 364         GenerateEnterAndExitFunctionCode(currentFunction);
 365         compoundLevel = 0;
 366         functionNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 367         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 368         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 369         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 370         boundFunction->SetBody(std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 371         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(functionSymbol, functionNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 372         boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundFunction));
 373     }
 374     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(functionNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 375     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 376     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 377 }
 378 
 379 void StatementBinder::Visit(StaticConstructorNode& staticConstructorNode)
 380 {
 381     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 382     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&staticConstructorNode);
 383     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::staticConstructorSymbol,  "static constructor symbol expected");
 384     StaticConstructorSymbol* staticConstructorSymbol = static_cast<StaticConstructorSymbol*>(symbol);
 385     if (!dontCheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols)
 386     {
 387         staticConstructorSymbol->FunctionGroup()->CheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols();
 388     }
 389     StaticConstructorSymbol* prevStaticConstructorSymbol = currentStaticConstructorSymbol;
 390     currentStaticConstructorSymbol = staticConstructorSymbol;
 391     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 392     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(&boundCompileUnit, staticConstructorSymbol));
 393     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 394     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 395     if (staticConstructorNode.Body())
 396     {
 397         GenerateEnterAndExitFunctionCode(currentFunction);
 398         StaticConstructorNode* prevStaticConstructorNode = currentStaticConstructorNode;
 399         currentStaticConstructorNode = &staticConstructorNode;
 400         compoundLevel = 0;
 401         staticConstructorNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 402         currentStaticConstructorNode = prevStaticConstructorNode;
 403         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 404         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 405         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 406         boundFunction->SetBody(std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 407         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(staticConstructorSymbol, staticConstructorNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 408         currentClass->AddMember(std::move(boundFunction));
 409     }
 410     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(staticConstructorNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 411     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 412     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 413     currentStaticConstructorSymbol = prevStaticConstructorSymbol;
 414 }
 415 
 416 void StatementBinder::GenerateEnterAndExitFunctionCode(BoundFunction* boundFunction)
 417 {
 418     Span span;
 419     if (boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->DontThrow()) return;
 420     TypeSymbol* systemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSystemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol();
 421     if (systemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol == nullptr)
 422     {
 423         sngcm::ast::IdentifierNode systemRuntimeUnwindInfoNode(span, U"System.Runtime.UnwindInfo");
 424         systemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol = ResolveType(&systemRuntimeUnwindInfoNode, boundCompileUnit, containerScope);
 425         boundCompileUnit.SetSystemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol(systemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol);
 426     }
 427     FunctionSymbol* initUnwindSymbol = boundCompileUnit.GetInitUnwindInfoFunctionSymbol();
 428     if (initUnwindSymbol == nullptr)
 429     {
 430         boundCompileUnit.GenerateInitUnwindInfoFunctionSymbol();
 431     }
 432     LocalVariableSymbol* prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol = new LocalVariableSymbol(span, U"@prevUnwindInfo");
 433     containerScope->Install(prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 434     prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol->SetType(systemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol->AddPointer(span));
 435     boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->SetPrevUnwindInfoVar(prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 436     sngcm::ast::IdentifierNode* prevUnwindInfoNode1 = new IdentifierNode(span, U"@prevUnwindInfo");
 437     symbolTable.MapSymbol(prevUnwindInfoNode1, prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 438     symbolTable.MapNode(prevUnwindInfoNode1, prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 439     sngcm::ast::InvokeNode* pushUnwindInfo = new sngcm::ast::InvokeNode(span, new sngcm::ast::IdentifierNode(span, U"RtPushUnwindInfo"));
 440     LocalVariableSymbol* unwindInfoVariableSymbol = new LocalVariableSymbol(span, U"@unwindInfo");
 441     containerScope->Install(unwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 442     unwindInfoVariableSymbol->SetType(systemRuntimeUnwindInfoSymbol);
 443     boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->SetUnwindInfoVar(unwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 444     sngcm::ast::IdentifierNode* unwindInfoNode1 = new IdentifierNode(span, U"@unwindInfo");
 445     symbolTable.MapSymbol(unwindInfoNode1, unwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 446     symbolTable.MapNode(unwindInfoNode1, unwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 447     pushUnwindInfo->AddArgument(new sngcm::ast::CastNode(span, new sngcm::ast::PointerNode(span, new sngcm::ast::VoidNode(span)), new AddrOfNode(span, unwindInfoNode1)));
 448     sngcm::ast::AssignmentStatementNode assignUnwindInfo(span, prevUnwindInfoNode1, 
 449         new sngcm::ast::CastNode(span, new PointerNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"System.Runtime.UnwindInfo")), pushUnwindInfo));
 450     assignUnwindInfo.Accept(*this);
 451     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> pushUnwindInfoStatement(statement.release());
 452 
 453     sngcm::ast::IdentifierNode* prevUnwindInfoNode2 = new IdentifierNode(span, U"@prevUnwindInfo");
 454     symbolTable.MapSymbol(prevUnwindInfoNode2, prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 455     symbolTable.MapNode(prevUnwindInfoNode2, prevUnwindInfoVariableSymbol);
 456     sngcm::ast::IdentifierNode* unwindInfoNode2 = new IdentifierNode(span, U"@unwindInfo");

 512 void StatementBinder::Visit(ConstructorNode& constructorNode)
 513 {
 514     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 515     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&constructorNode);
 516     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::constructorSymbol, "constructor symbol expected");
 517     ConstructorSymbol* constructorSymbol = static_cast<ConstructorSymbol*>(symbol);
 518     if (!dontCheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols)
 519     {
 520         constructorSymbol->FunctionGroup()->CheckDuplicateFunctionSymbols();
 521     }
 522     ConstructorSymbol* prevConstructorSymbol = currentConstructorSymbol;
 523     currentConstructorSymbol = constructorSymbol;
 524     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 525     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(&boundCompileUnit, constructorSymbol));
 526     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 527     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 528     if (constructorNode.Body())
 529     {
 530         GenerateEnterAndExitFunctionCode(currentFunction);
 531         ConstructorNode* prevConstructorNode = currentConstructorNode;
 532         currentConstructorNode = &constructorNode;
 533         compoundLevel = 0;
 534         constructorNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 535         currentConstructorNode = prevConstructorNode;

 539         boundFunction->SetBody(std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 540     }
 541     else if (constructorSymbol->IsDefault())
 542     {
 543         ConstructorNode* prevConstructorNode = currentConstructorNode;
 544         currentConstructorNode = &constructorNode;
 545         std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement> boundCompoundStatement(new BoundCompoundStatement(module, constructorNode.GetSpan()));
 546         GenerateClassInitialization(currentConstructorSymbol, currentConstructorNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, true, constructorNode.GetSpan());
 547         currentConstructorNode = prevConstructorNode;
 548         boundFunction->SetBody(std::move(boundCompoundStatement));
 549     }
 550     if (boundFunction->Body())
 551     {
 552         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(constructorSymbol, constructorNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 553         currentClass->AddMember(std::move(boundFunction));
 554     }
 555     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(constructorNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 556     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 557     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 558     currentConstructorSymbol = prevConstructorSymbol;
 559 }

 695 void StatementBinder::Visit(CompoundStatementNode& compoundStatementNode)
 696 {
 697     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 698     Symbol* symbol = symbolTable.GetSymbol(&compoundStatementNode);
 699     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::declarationBlock, "declaration block expected");
 700     DeclarationBlock* declarationBlock = static_cast<DeclarationBlock*>(symbol);
 701     containerScope = declarationBlock->GetContainerScope();
 702     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement> boundCompoundStatement(new BoundCompoundStatement(module, compoundStatementNode.BeginBraceSpan(), compoundStatementNode.EndBraceSpan()));
 703     if (compoundLevel == 0)
 704     {
 705         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::profile))
 706         {
 707             bool profile = true;
 708             if (currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->IsProgramMain())
 709             {
 710                 profile = false;
 711             }
 712             else if (currentClass && currentClass->GetClassTypeSymbol()->FullName() == U"System.Runtime.FunctionProfiler")
 713             {
 714                 profile = false;
 715             }
 716             if (profile)
 717             {
 718                 boost::uuids::uuid functionId = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->FunctionId();
 719                 symbolTable.MapProfiledFunction(functionId, currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->FullName());
 720                 ConstructionStatementNode constructFunctionProfiler(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), new IdentifierNode(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), U"System.Runtime.FunctionProfiler"), 
 721                     new IdentifierNode(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), U"@functionProfiler"));
 722                 constructFunctionProfiler.AddArgument(new UuidLiteralNode(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), functionId));
 723                 symbolTable.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
 724                 symbolTable.BeginContainer(containerScope->Container());
 725                 SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreatorVisitor(symbolTable);
 726                 constructFunctionProfiler.Accept(symbolCreatorVisitor);
 727                 symbolTable.EndContainer();
 728                 TypeBinder typeBinder(boundCompileUnit);
 729                 typeBinder.SetContainerScope(containerScope);
 730                 typeBinder.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
 731                 constructFunctionProfiler.Accept(typeBinder);
 732                 constructFunctionProfiler.Accept(*this);
 733                 boundCompoundStatement->AddStatement(std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(ReleaseStatement()));
 734             }
 735         }
 736         if (currentStaticConstructorSymbol && currentStaticConstructorNode)
 737         {
 738             GenerateStaticClassInitialization(currentStaticConstructorSymbol, currentStaticConstructorNode, boundCompileUnit, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, containerScope, this, 
 739                 boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan());
 740         }
 741         else if (currentConstructorSymbol && currentConstructorNode)
 742         {
 743             GenerateClassInitialization(currentConstructorSymbol, currentConstructorNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, false, 
 744                 boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan());
 745         }
 746         else if (currentMemberFunctionSymbol && currentMemberFunctionSymbol->GroupName() == U"operator=" && currentMemberFunctionNode)
 747         {
 748             GenerateClassAssignment(currentMemberFunctionSymbol, currentMemberFunctionNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, false, 
 749                 boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan());
 750         }
 751         else if (currentMemberFunctionSymbol && currentMemberFunctionSymbol->IsStatic() && currentMemberFunctionNode)
 752         {
 753             if (currentClass->GetClassTypeSymbol()->StaticConstructor())
 754             {
 755                 boundCompoundStatement->AddStatement(std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundInitializationStatement(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(
 756                     new BoundFunctionCall(module, boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan(), currentClass->GetClassTypeSymbol()->StaticConstructor())))));
 757             }
 758         }
 759     }
 760     ++compoundLevel;
 761     int n = compoundStatementNode.Statements().Count();
 762     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 763     {
 764         StatementNode* statementNode = compoundStatementNode.Statements()[i];
 765         statementNode->Accept(*this);
 766         boundCompoundStatement->AddStatement(std::move(statement));
 767     }
 768     --compoundLevel;
 769     if (compoundLevel == 0 && currentDestructorSymbol && currentDestructorNode)
 770     {
 771         GenerateClassTermination(currentDestructorSymbol, currentDestructorNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, boundCompoundStatement->EndSpan());
 772     }
 773     AddStatement(boundCompoundStatement.release());
 774     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 775 }
 776 
 777 void StatementBinder::Visit(ReturnStatementNode& returnStatementNode)
 778 {
 779     if (returnStatementNode.Expression())
 780     {
 781         if (currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnsClassInterfaceOrClassDelegateByValue())
 782         {
 783             std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> classReturnLookups;
 784             classReturnLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 785             classReturnLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType()->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
 786             classReturnLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 787             std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>classReturnArgs;
 788             classReturnArgs.push_back(std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnParam())));
 789             TypeSymbol* returnType = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 790             bool returnClassDelegateType = returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classDelegateTypeSymbol;
 791             std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> expression = BindExpression(returnStatementNode.Expression(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this, false, returnClassDelegateType, 
 792                 returnClassDelegateType);
 793             bool exceptionCapture = false;
 794             if (insideCatch && expression->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 795             {
 796                 exceptionCapture = true;
 797             }
 798             if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundLocalVariable)
 799             {
 800                 std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> rvalueLookups;
 801                 rvalueLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 802                 rvalueLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 803                 std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>rvalueArguments;
 804                 if (returnClassDelegateType && expression->GetType()->BaseType()->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::functionGroupTypeSymbol)
 805                 {
 806                     TypeSymbol* exprType = expression->GetType();
 807                     ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
 808                     expression.reset(new BoundConversion(module, std::move(expression), boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(exprType, returnType, containerScope, currentFunction, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), argumentMatch)));
 809                 }
 810                 rvalueArguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
 811                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> rvalueExpr = ResolveOverload(U"System.Rvalue", containerScope, rvalueLookups, rvalueArguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
 812                     returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 813                 expression = std::move(rvalueExpr);
 814             }
 815             classReturnArgs.push_back(std::move(expression));
 816             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> constructorCall = ResolveOverload(U"@constructor", containerScope, classReturnLookups, classReturnArgs, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
 817                 returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 818             std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> constructStatement(new BoundInitializationStatement(module, std::move(constructorCall)));
 819             AddStatement(constructStatement.release());
 820             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> returnFunctionCall;
 821             std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> returnStatement(new BoundReturnStatement(module, std::move(returnFunctionCall), returnStatementNode.GetSpan()));
 822             if (exceptionCapture)
 823             {
 824                 AddReleaseExceptionStatement(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 825             }
 826             AddStatement(returnStatement.release());
 827         }
 828         else
 829         {
 830             TypeSymbol* returnType = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 831             bool returnDelegateType = false;
 832             bool returnClassDelegateType = false;
 833             bool exceptionCapture = false;
 834             if (returnType)
 835             {
 836                 returnDelegateType = returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::delegateTypeSymbol;
 837                 returnClassDelegateType = returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classDelegateTypeSymbol;
 838             }
 839             if (returnType && returnType->GetSymbolType() != SymbolType::voidTypeSymbol)
 840             {
 841                 std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>returnTypeArgs;
 842                 BoundTypeExpression* boundTypeExpression = new BoundTypeExpression(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), returnType);
 843                 returnTypeArgs.push_back(std::unique_ptr<BoundTypeExpression>(boundTypeExpression));
 844                 std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
 845                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 846                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, returnType->BaseType()->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
 847                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 848                 std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> returnFunctionCall = ResolveOverload(U"@return", containerScope, functionScopeLookups, returnTypeArgs, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
 849                     returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 850                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> expression = BindExpression(returnStatementNode.Expression(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this, false, 
 851                     returnDelegateType || returnClassDelegateType, returnClassDelegateType);
 852                 if (insideCatch && expression->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 853                 {
 854                     exceptionCapture = true;
 855                 }
 856                 std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>returnValueArguments;
 857                 returnValueArguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
 858                 FunctionMatch functionMatch(returnFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
 859                 bool conversionFound = FindConversions(boundCompileUnit, returnFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol(), returnValueArguments, functionMatch, ConversionType::implicit_, 
 860                     containerScope, currentFunction, returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 861                 if (conversionFound)
 862                 {
 863                     Assert(!functionMatch.argumentMatches.empty(), "argument match expected");
 864                     ArgumentMatch argumentMatch = functionMatch.argumentMatches[0];
 865                     if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags != OperationFlags::none)
 866                     {
 867                         if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::addr)
 868                         {
 869                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->AddLvalueReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 870                             BoundAddressOfExpression* addressOfExpression = new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 871                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(addressOfExpression);
 872                         }
 873                         else if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::deref)
 874                         {
 875                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 876                             BoundDereferenceExpression* dereferenceExpression = new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 877                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(dereferenceExpression);
 878                         }
 879                     }
 880                     FunctionSymbol* conversionFun = argumentMatch.conversionFun;
 881                     if (conversionFun)
 882                     {
 883                         if (conversionFun->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::constructorSymbol)
 884                         {
 885                             BoundFunctionCall* constructorCall = new BoundFunctionCall(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), conversionFun);
 886                             LocalVariableSymbol* temporary = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->CreateTemporary(conversionFun->ConversionTargetType(), returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 887                             constructorCall->AddArgument(std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), temporary)), 
 888                                 conversionFun->ConversionTargetType()->AddPointer(returnStatementNode.GetSpan()))));
 889                             constructorCall->AddArgument(std::move(returnValueArguments[0]));
 890                             BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression* conversion = new BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(constructorCall), 
 891                                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), temporary)));
 892                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(conversion);
 893                         }
 894                         else
 895                         {
 896                             BoundConversion* boundConversion = new BoundConversion(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(returnValueArguments[0].release()), conversionFun);
 897                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(boundConversion);
 898                         }
 899                     }
 900                     if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags != OperationFlags::none)
 901                     {
 902                         if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::addr)
 903                         {
 904                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->AddLvalueReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 905                             BoundAddressOfExpression* addressOfExpression = new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 906                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(addressOfExpression);
 907                         }
 908                         else if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::deref)
 909                         {
 910                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 911                             BoundDereferenceExpression* dereferenceExpression = new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 912                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(dereferenceExpression);
 913                         }
 914                     }
 915                     returnFunctionCall->SetArguments(std::move(returnValueArguments));
 916                 }
 917                 else
 918                 {
 919                     throw Exception(module, "no implicit conversion from '" + ToUtf8(returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->FullName()) + "' to '" + ToUtf8(returnType->FullName()) + "' exists", 
 920                         returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 921                 }
 922                 CheckAccess(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), returnFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
 923                 if (exceptionCapture)
 924                 {
 925                     AddReleaseExceptionStatement(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 926                 }
 927                 AddStatement(new BoundReturnStatement(module, std::move(returnFunctionCall), returnStatementNode.GetSpan()));
 928             }
 929             else
 930             {
 931                 if (returnType)
 932                 {
 933                     throw Exception(module, "void function cannot return a value", returnStatementNode.Expression()->GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 934                 }
 935                 else
 936                 {
 937                     throw Exception(module, "constructor or assignment function cannot return a value", returnStatementNode.Expression()->GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 938                 }
 939             }
 940         }
 941     }
 942     else
 943     {
 944         TypeSymbol* returnType = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 945         if (!returnType || returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::voidTypeSymbol)
 946         {
 947             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> returnFunctionCall;
 948             AddStatement(new BoundReturnStatement(module, std::move(returnFunctionCall), returnStatementNode.GetSpan()));
 949         }
 950         else
 951         {
 952             throw Exception(module, "nonvoid function must return a value", returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 953         }
 954     }
 955 }

 957 void StatementBinder::Visit(IfStatementNode& ifStatementNode)
 958 {
 959     bool exceptionCapture = false;
 960     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition = BindExpression(ifStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
 961     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 962     {
 963         exceptionCapture = true;
 964     }
 965     if (!TypesEqual(symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"bool"), condition->GetType()->PlainType(ifStatementNode.GetSpan())))
 966     {
 967         throw Exception(module, "condition of an if statement must be a Boolean expression", ifStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
 968     }
 969     if (condition->GetType()->IsReferenceType())
 970     {
 971         TypeSymbol* baseType = condition->GetType()->BaseType();
 972         condition.reset(new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(condition), baseType));
 973     }
 974     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> s;
 975     if (statement)
 976     {
 977         s = std::move(statement);
 978     }
 979     ifStatementNode.ThenS()->Accept(*this);
 980     BoundStatement* thenS = statement.release();
 981     BoundStatement* elseS = nullptr;
 982     if (ifStatementNode.ElseS())
 983     {
 984         ifStatementNode.ElseS()->Accept(*this);
 985         elseS = statement.release();
 986     }
 987     if (s)
 988     {
 989         AddStatement(s.release());
 990     }
 991     if (exceptionCapture)
 992     {
 993         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(ifStatementNode.GetSpan());
 994     }
 995     AddStatement(new BoundIfStatement(module, ifStatementNode.GetSpan(), std::move(condition), std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(thenS), std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(elseS)));
 996 }

1068 void StatementBinder::Visit(ForStatementNode& forStatementNode)
1069 {
1070     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
1071     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&forStatementNode);
1072     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::declarationBlock, "declaration block expected");
1073     DeclarationBlock* declarationBlock = static_cast<DeclarationBlock*>(symbol);
1074     containerScope = declarationBlock->GetContainerScope();
1075     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition;
1076     if (forStatementNode.Condition())
1077     {
1078         condition = BindExpression(forStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1079     }
1080     else
1081     {
1082         BooleanLiteralNode trueNode(forStatementNode.GetSpan(), true);
1083         condition = BindExpression(&trueNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1084     }
1085     bool exceptionCapture = false;
1086     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1087     {
1088         exceptionCapture = true;
1089     }
1090     if (!TypesEqual(symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"bool"), condition->GetType()->PlainType(forStatementNode.GetSpan())))
1091     {
1092         throw Exception(module, "condition of a for statement must be a Boolean expression", forStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
1093     }
1094     if (condition->GetType()->IsReferenceType())
1095     {
1096         TypeSymbol* baseType = condition->GetType()->BaseType();
1097         condition.reset(new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(condition), baseType));
1098     }
1099     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> s;
1100     if (statement)
1101     {
1102         s = std::move(statement);
1103     }
1104     forStatementNode.InitS()->Accept(*this);
1105     BoundStatement* initS = statement.release();
1106     forStatementNode.LoopS()->Accept(*this);
1107     BoundStatement* loopS = statement.release();
1108     loopS->SetForLoopStatementNode();
1109     forStatementNode.ActionS()->Accept(*this);
1110     BoundStatement* actionS = statement.release();
1111     if (s)
1112     {
1113         AddStatement(s.release());
1114     }
1115     if (exceptionCapture)
1116     {
1117         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(forStatementNode.GetSpan());
1118     }
1119     AddStatement(new BoundForStatement(module, forStatementNode.GetSpan(), std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(initS), std::move(condition), std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(loopS), 
1120         std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(actionS)));
1121     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1122 }

1124 void StatementBinder::Visit(BreakStatementNode& breakStatementNode)
1125 {

1131     }

1145     {

1148     AddStatement(new BoundBreakStatement(module, breakStatementNode.GetSpan()));
1149 }

1185 void StatementBinder::Visit(ConstructionStatementNode& constructionStatementNode)
1186 {
1187     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&constructionStatementNode);
1188     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::localVariableSymbol, "local variable symbol expected");
1189     LocalVariableSymbol* localVariableSymbol = static_cast<LocalVariableSymbol*>(symbol);
1190     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>arguments;
1191     BoundExpression* localVariable = new BoundLocalVariable(module, constructionStatementNode.GetSpan(), localVariableSymbol);
1192     arguments.push_back(std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, 
1193         std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(localVariable), localVariable->GetType()->AddPointer(constructionStatementNode.GetSpan()))));
1194     bool constructDelegateOrClassDelegateType =
1195         localVariableSymbol->GetType()->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::delegateTypeSymbol || 
1196         localVariableSymbol->GetType()->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classDelegateTypeSymbol;
1197     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
1198     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, localVariableSymbol->GetType()->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
1199     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
1200     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
1201     bool exceptionCapture = false;
1202     int n = constructionStatementNode.Arguments().Count();
1203     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1204     {
1205         Node* argumentNode = constructionStatementNode.Arguments()[i];
1206         std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> argument = BindExpression(argumentNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this, false, constructDelegateOrClassDelegateType);
1207         if (insideCatch && argument->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1208         {
1209             exceptionCapture = true;
1210         }
1211         arguments.push_back(std::move(argument));
1212     }
1213     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> constructorCall = ResolveOverload(U"@constructor", containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
1214         constructionStatementNode.GetSpan());
1215     FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol = constructorCall->GetFunctionSymbol();
1216     CheckAccess(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), functionSymbol);
1217     if (exceptionCapture)
1218     {
1219         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(constructionStatementNode.GetSpan());
1220     }
1221     if (functionSymbol->Parent()->IsClassTypeSymbol())
1222     {
1223         ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(functionSymbol->Parent());
1224         if (classType->Destructor() && classType->Destructor()->IsGeneratedFunction() && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::info))
1225         {
1226             if (!boundCompileUnit.IsGeneratedDestructorInstantiated(classType->Destructor()))
1227             {
1228                 boundCompileUnit.SetGeneratedDestructorInstantiated(classType->Destructor());
1229                 std::unique_ptr<BoundClass> boundClass(new BoundClass(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule(), classType));
1230                 GenerateDestructorImplementation(boundClass.get(), classType->Destructor(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope, currentFunction, 
1231                     constructionStatementNode.GetSpan());
1232                 boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundClass));
1233             }
1234         }
1235     }
1236     BoundConstructionStatement* boundConstructionStatement = new BoundConstructionStatement(module, std::move(constructorCall), constructionStatementNode.GetSpan());
1237     boundConstructionStatement->SetLocalVariable(localVariableSymbol);
1238     AddStatement(boundConstructionStatement);
1239 }

1241 void StatementBinder::Visit(DeleteStatementNode& deleteStatementNode)
1242 {
1243     Span span;
1244     if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::llvm)
1245     {
1246         span = deleteStatementNode.GetSpan();
1247     }
1248     bool exceptionCapture = false;
1249     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> ptr = BindExpression(deleteStatementNode.Expression(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1250     if (insideCatch && ptr->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1251     {
1252         exceptionCapture = true;
1253     }
1254     if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::llvm || GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::cmcpp)
1255     {
1256         if (GetConfig() == "debug")
1257         {
1258             std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> lookups;
1259             lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
1260             lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
1261             std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>arguments;
1262             arguments.push_back(std::move(std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(ptr->Clone())));
1263             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> disposeCall = ResolveOverload(U"RtDispose", containerScope, lookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, span);
1264             CheckAccess(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), disposeCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
1265             AddStatement(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, std::move(disposeCall), span));
1266         }
1267     }
1268     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> memFreePtr;
1269     TypeSymbol* baseType = ptr->GetType()->BaseType();
1270     if (baseType->HasNontrivialDestructor())
1271     {
1272         Assert(baseType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTypeSymbol || baseType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTemplateSpecializationSymbol, "class type expected");
1273         ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(baseType);
1274         std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> lookups;
1275         lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
1276         lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, classType->ClassInterfaceOrNsScope()));
1277         lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
1278         std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>arguments;
1279         arguments.push_back(std::move(ptr));
1280         std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> destructorCall = ResolveOverload(U"@destructor", containerScope, lookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, span);
1281         CheckAccess(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), destructorCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
1282         if (destructorCall->GetFunctionSymbol()->IsVirtualAbstractOrOverride())
1283         {
1284             destructorCall->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::virtualCall);
1285         }
1286         AddStatement(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, std::move(destructorCall), span));
1287         memFreePtr = BindExpression(deleteStatementNode.Expression(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1288         if (insideCatch && memFreePtr->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1289         {
1290             exceptionCapture = true;
1291         }
1292     }
1293     else
1294     {
1295         memFreePtr = std::move(ptr);
1296     }
1297     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> lookups;
1298     lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
1299     lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
1300     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>arguments;
1301     arguments.push_back(std::move(memFreePtr));
1302     const char32_t* memFreeFunctionName = U"";
1303     if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::llvm || GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::cmcpp)
1304     {
1305         memFreeFunctionName = U"RtMemFree";
1306     }
1307     else if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::cmsx)
1308     {
1309         memFreeFunctionName = U"MemFree";
1310     }
1311     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> memFreeCall = ResolveOverload(memFreeFunctionName, containerScope, lookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, span);
1312     CheckAccess(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), memFreeCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
1313     if (exceptionCapture)
1314     {
1315         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(deleteStatementNode.GetSpan());
1316     }
1317     AddStatement(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, std::move(memFreeCall), deleteStatementNode.GetSpan()));
1318 }

1320 void StatementBinder::Visit(DestroyStatementNode& destroyStatementNode)
1321 {
1322     bool exceptionCapture = false;
1323     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> ptr = BindExpression(destroyStatementNode.Expression(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1324     if (insideCatch && ptr->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1325     {
1326         exceptionCapture = true;
1327     }

1340         lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));

1342         arguments.push_back(std::move(ptr));

1347             destructorCall->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::virtualCall);
1348         }
1349         if (exceptionCapture)
1350         {
1351             AddReleaseExceptionStatement(destroyStatementNode.GetSpan());
1352         }
1353         AddStatement(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, std::move(destructorCall), destroyStatementNode.GetSpan()));
1354     }
1355     else
1356     {
1357         AddStatement(new BoundEmptyStatement(module, destroyStatementNode.GetSpan()));

1361 void StatementBinder::Visit(AssignmentStatementNode& assignmentStatementNode)
1362 {
1363     bool exceptionCapture = false;
1364     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> target = BindExpression(assignmentStatementNode.TargetExpr(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this, true);
1365     if (insideCatch && target->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1366     {
1367         exceptionCapture = true;
1368     }
1369     TypeSymbol* targetPlainType = target->GetType()->PlainType(assignmentStatementNode.GetSpan());

1381     }
1382     else

1385     }
1386     TypeSymbol* targetType = target->GetType()->BaseType();

1389     if (insideCatch && source->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1390     {
1391         exceptionCapture = true;
1392     }
1393     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>arguments;
1394     arguments.push_back(std::move(target));
1395     arguments.push_back(std::move(source));
1396     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
1397     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, targetType->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
1398     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
1399     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
1400     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> assignmentCall = ResolveOverload(U"operator=", containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
1401         assignmentStatementNode.GetSpan());
1402     CheckAccess(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), assignmentCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
1403     currentFunction->MoveTemporaryDestructorCallsTo(*assignmentCall);
1404     if (exceptionCapture)
1405     {
1406         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(assignmentStatementNode.GetSpan());
1407     }
1408     AddStatement(new BoundAssignmentStatement(module, std::move(assignmentCall), assignmentStatementNode.GetSpan()));
1409 }

1431 void StatementBinder::Visit(RangeForStatementNode& rangeForStatementNode)
1432 {
1433     Span span;
1434     if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::llvm)
1435     {
1436         span = rangeForStatementNode.GetSpan();
1437     }
1438     Span actionBeginBraceSpan;
1439     Span actionEndBraceSpan;
1440     if (rangeForStatementNode.Action()->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
1441     {
1442         CompoundStatementNode* action = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Action());
1443         actionBeginBraceSpan = action->BeginBraceSpan();
1444         actionEndBraceSpan = action->EndBraceSpan();
1445     }
1446     else
1447     {
1448         actionBeginBraceSpan = rangeForStatementNode.Action()->GetSpan();
1449         actionEndBraceSpan = rangeForStatementNode.Action()->GetSpan();
1450     }
1451     Span initSpan = rangeForStatementNode.TypeExpr()->GetSpan();
1452     initSpan.end = rangeForStatementNode.Id()->GetSpan().end;
1453     Span containerSpan = rangeForStatementNode.Container()->GetSpan();
1454     Span colonSpan = rangeForStatementNode.ColonSpan();

1456     TypeSymbol* plainContainerType = container->GetType()->PlainType(span);
1457     std::u32string plainContainerTypeFullName = plainContainerType->FullName();
1458     ParsingContext parsingContext;
1459     CmajorLexer cmajorLexer(plainContainerTypeFullName + U"\n", "", 0);
1460     cmajorLexer.SetSeparatorChar('\n');
1461     std::unique_ptr<Node> containerTypeNode(TypeExprParser::Parse(cmajorLexer, &parsingContext));
1462     std::unique_ptr<IdentifierNode> iteratorTypeNode = nullptr;
1463     if (container->GetType()->IsConstType())
1464     {
1465         iteratorTypeNode.reset(new IdentifierNode(span, U"ConstIterator"));
1466     }
1467     else
1468     {
1469         iteratorTypeNode.reset(new IdentifierNode(span, U"Iterator"));
1470     }
1471     CloneContext cloneContext;
1472     SpanMapper spanMapper;
1473     cloneContext.SetSpanMapper(&spanMapper);
1474     std::unique_ptr<CompoundStatementNode> compoundStatementNode(new CompoundStatementNode(span));
1475     if (rangeForStatementNode.Action()->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
1476     {
1477         CompoundStatementNode* action = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Action());
1478         compoundStatementNode->SetBeginBraceSpan(span);
1479         compoundStatementNode->SetEndBraceSpan(span);
1480     }
1481     else
1482     {
1483         compoundStatementNode->SetBeginBraceSpan(span);
1484         compoundStatementNode->SetEndBraceSpan(span);
1485     }
1486     compoundStatementNode->SetParent(rangeForStatementNode.Parent());
1487     ConstructionStatementNode* constructEndIteratorStatement = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, 
1488         new DotNode(span, containerTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext), static_cast<IdentifierNode*>(iteratorTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext))), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@end"));
1489     if (container->GetType()->IsConstType())
1490     {
1491         constructEndIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"CEnd"))));
1492     }
1493     else
1494     {
1495         constructEndIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"End"))));
1496     }
1497     compoundStatementNode->AddStatement(constructEndIteratorStatement);
1498     ConstructionStatementNode* constructIteratorStatement = new ConstructionStatementNode(initSpan, 
1499         new DotNode(span, containerTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext), static_cast<IdentifierNode*>(iteratorTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext))), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@it"));
1500     if (container->GetType()->IsConstType())
1501     {
1502         constructIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"CBegin"))));
1503     }
1504     else
1505     {
1506         constructIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"Begin"))));
1507     }
1508     Node* itNotEndCond = new NotEqualNode(colonSpan, new IdentifierNode(colonSpan, U"@it"), new IdentifierNode(colonSpan, U"@end"));
1509     StatementNode* incrementItStatement = new ExpressionStatementNode(containerSpan, new PrefixIncrementNode(containerSpan, new IdentifierNode(containerSpan, U"@it")));
1510     CompoundStatementNode* actionStatement = new CompoundStatementNode(actionBeginBraceSpan);
1511     actionStatement->SetBeginBraceSpan(actionBeginBraceSpan);
1512     actionStatement->SetEndBraceSpan(actionEndBraceSpan);
1513     ConstructionStatementNode* constructLoopVarStatement = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, 
1514         rangeForStatementNode.TypeExpr()->Clone(cloneContext), static_cast<IdentifierNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Id()->Clone(cloneContext)));
1515     constructLoopVarStatement->AddArgument(new DerefNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@it")));
1516     actionStatement->AddStatement(constructLoopVarStatement);
1517     actionStatement->AddStatement(static_cast<StatementNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Action()->Clone(cloneContext)));
1518     ForStatementNode* forStatement = new ForStatementNode(span, constructIteratorStatement, itNotEndCond, incrementItStatement, actionStatement);
1519     compoundStatementNode->AddStatement(forStatement);
1520 
1521     symbolTable.BeginContainer(containerScope->Container());
1522     SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreatorVisitor(symbolTable);
1523     compoundStatementNode->Accept(symbolCreatorVisitor);
1524     symbolTable.EndContainer();
1525     TypeBinder typeBinder(boundCompileUnit);
1526     typeBinder.SetContainerScope(containerScope);
1527     typeBinder.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
1528     compoundStatementNode->Accept(typeBinder);
1529     compoundStatementNode->Accept(*this);
1530 }

1532 void StatementBinder::Visit(SwitchStatementNode& switchStatementNode)
1533 {
1534     bool exceptionCapture = false;
1535     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition = BindExpression(switchStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1536     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1537     {
1538         exceptionCapture = true;
1539     }
1540     TypeSymbol* conditionType = condition->GetType();
1541     if (conditionType->IsSwitchConditionType())
1542     {
1543         if (conditionType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::enumTypeSymbol)
1544         {
1545             EnumTypeSymbol* enumType = static_cast<EnumTypeSymbol*>(conditionType);
1546             conditionType = enumType->UnderlyingType();
1547         }
1548         TypeSymbol* prevSwitchConditionType = switchConditionType;
1549         switchConditionType = conditionType;
1550         std::std::unordered_map<IntegralValue, CaseStatementNode*, IntegralValueHash>*prevCaseValueMap=currentCaseValueMap;
1551         std::unordered_map<IntegralValue, CaseStatementNode*, IntegralValueHash> caseValueMap;
1552         currentCaseValueMap = &caseValueMap;
1553         std::std::vector<std::std::pair<BoundGotoCaseStatement*, IntegralValue>>*prevGotoCaseStatements=currentGotoCaseStatements;
1554         std::vector<std::std::pair<BoundGotoCaseStatement*, IntegralValue>>gotoCaseStatements;
1555         currentGotoCaseStatements = &gotoCaseStatements;
1556         std::std::vector<BoundGotoDefaultStatement*>*prevGotoDefaultStatements=currentGotoDefaultStatements;
1557         std::vector<BoundGotoDefaultStatement*> gotoDefaultStatements;
1558         currentGotoDefaultStatements = &gotoDefaultStatements;
1559         std::unique_ptr<BoundSwitchStatement> boundSwitchStatement(new BoundSwitchStatement(module, switchStatementNode.GetSpan(), std::move(condition)));
1560         int n = switchStatementNode.Cases().Count();
1561         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1562         {
1563             CaseStatementNode* caseS = switchStatementNode.Cases()[i];
1564             caseS->Accept(*this);
1565             Assert(statement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCaseStatement, "case statement expected");
1566             boundSwitchStatement->AddCaseStatement(std::unique_ptr<BoundCaseStatement>(static_cast<BoundCaseStatement*>(statement.release())));
1567         }
1568         if (switchStatementNode.Default())
1569         {
1570             switchStatementNode.Default()->Accept(*this);
1571             Assert(statement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundDefaultStatement, "default statement expected");
1572             boundSwitchStatement->SetDefaultStatement(std::unique_ptr<BoundDefaultStatement>(static_cast<BoundDefaultStatement*>(statement.release())));
1573         }
1574         for (const std::std::pair<BoundGotoCaseStatement*, IntegralValue>&p : gotoCaseStatements)
1575         {
1576             BoundGotoCaseStatement* gotoCaseStatement = p.first;
1577             IntegralValue integralCaseValue = p.second;
1578             auto it = caseValueMap.find(integralCaseValue);
1579             if (it == caseValueMap.cend())
1580             {
1581                 throw Exception(module, "case not found", gotoCaseStatement->GetSpan());
1582             }
1583         }
1584         if (!gotoDefaultStatements.empty() && !switchStatementNode.Default())
1585         {
1586             throw Exception(module, "switch does not have a default statement", gotoDefaultStatements.front()->GetSpan());
1587         }
1588         currentGotoCaseStatements = prevGotoCaseStatements;
1589         currentGotoDefaultStatements = prevGotoDefaultStatements;
1590         currentCaseValueMap = prevCaseValueMap;
1591         if (exceptionCapture)
1592         {
1593             AddReleaseExceptionStatement(switchStatementNode.GetSpan());
1594         }
1595         AddStatement(boundSwitchStatement.release());
1596         switchConditionType = prevSwitchConditionType;
1597     }
1598     else
1599     {
1600         throw Exception(module, "switch statement condition must be of integer, character, enumerated or Boolean type", switchStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
1601     }
1602 }

1604 void StatementBinder::Visit(CaseStatementNode& caseStatementNode)
1605 {
1606     std::unique_ptr<BoundCaseStatement> boundCaseStatement(new BoundCaseStatement(module, caseStatementNode.GetSpan()));
1607     bool terminated = false;
1608     int n = caseStatementNode.Statements().Count();
1609     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1610     {
1611         StatementNode* statementNode = caseStatementNode.Statements()[i];
1612         if (TerminatesCase(statementNode))
1613         {
1614             terminated = true;
1615         }
1616         statementNode->Accept(*this);
1617         boundCaseStatement->AddStatement(std::move(statement));
1618     }
1619     if (!terminated)
1620     {
1621         throw Exception(module, "case must end in break, continue, return, throw, goto, goto case or goto default statement", caseStatementNode.GetSpan());
1622     }
1623     int ne = caseStatementNode.CaseExprs().Count();
1624     for (int i = 0; i < ne; ++i)
1625     {
1626         Node* caseExprNode = caseStatementNode.CaseExprs()[i];
1627         std::unique_ptr<Value> caseValue = Evaluate(caseExprNode, switchConditionType, containerScope, boundCompileUnit, false, currentFunction, caseExprNode->GetSpan());
1628         IntegralValue integralCaseValue(caseValue.get());
1629         Assert(currentCaseValueMap, "current case value map not set");
1630         auto it = currentCaseValueMap->find(integralCaseValue);
1631         if (it != currentCaseValueMap->cend())
1632         {
1633             throw Exception(module, "case value already used", caseExprNode->GetSpan());
1634         }
1635         (*currentCaseValueMap)[integralCaseValue] = &caseStatementNode;
1636         boundCaseStatement->AddCaseValue(std::move(caseValue));
1637     }
1638     AddStatement(boundCaseStatement.release());
1639 }

1700 void StatementBinder::Visit(ThrowStatementNode& throwStatementNode)
1701 {
1702     bool prevCompilingThrow = compilingThrow;
1703     compilingThrow = true;
1704     if (currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->DontThrow() && !currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->HasTry())
1705     {
1706         throw Exception(module, "a nothrow function cannot contain a throw statement unless it handles exceptions", throwStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
1707     }
1708     Span span = throwStatementNode.GetSpan();
1709     Node* exceptionExprNode = throwStatementNode.Expression();
1710     if (exceptionExprNode)
1711     {
1712         std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> boundExceptionExpr = BindExpression(exceptionExprNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1713         if (boundExceptionExpr->GetType()->PlainType(span)->IsClassTypeSymbol())
1714         {
1715             ClassTypeSymbol* exceptionClassType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(boundExceptionExpr->GetType()->PlainType(span));
1716             IdentifierNode systemExceptionNode(throwStatementNode.GetSpan(), U"System.Exception");
1717             TypeSymbol* systemExceptionType = ResolveType(&systemExceptionNode, boundCompileUnit, containerScope);
1718             Assert(systemExceptionType->IsClassTypeSymbol(), "System.Exception not of class type");
1719             ClassTypeSymbol* systemExceptionClassType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(systemExceptionType);
1720             if (exceptionClassType == systemExceptionClassType || exceptionClassType->HasBaseClass(systemExceptionClassType))
1721             {
1722                 NewNode* newNode = new NewNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, exceptionClassType->FullName()));
1723                 CloneContext cloneContext;
1724                 SpanMapper spanMapper;
1725                 cloneContext.SetSpanMapper(&spanMapper);
1726                 newNode->AddArgument(throwStatementNode.Expression()->Clone(cloneContext));
1727                 if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::llvm || GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::cmcpp)
1728                 {
1729                     InvokeNode invokeNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"RtThrowException"));
1730                     invokeNode.AddArgument(newNode);
1731                     invokeNode.AddArgument(new UuidLiteralNode(span, exceptionClassType->TypeId()));
1732                     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> throwCallExpr = BindExpression(&invokeNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1733                     AddStatement(new BoundThrowStatement(module, span, std::move(throwCallExpr)));
1734                 }
1735                 else if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::cmsx)
1736                 {
1737                     InvokeNode invokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"System"), new IdentifierNode(span, U"Throw")));
1738                     invokeNode.AddArgument(newNode);
1739                     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> throwCallExpr = BindExpression(&invokeNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1740                     AddStatement(new BoundThrowStatement(module, span, std::move(throwCallExpr)));
1741                 }
1742             }
1743             else
1744             {
1745                 throw Exception(module, "exception class must be derived from System.Exception class", throwStatementNode.GetSpan());
1746             }
1747         }
1748         else
1749         {
1750             throw Exception(module, "exception not of class type", throwStatementNode.GetSpan());
1751         }
1752     }
1753     else
1754     {
1755         if (insideCatch)
1756         {
1757             InvokeNode invokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exPtr"), new IdentifierNode(span, U"Release")));
1758             std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> releaseCall = BindExpression(&invokeNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1759             AddStatement(new BoundRethrowStatement(module, span, std::move(releaseCall)));
1760         }
1761         else
1762         {
1763             throw Exception(module, "rethrow must occur inside a catch clause", throwStatementNode.GetSpan());
1764         }
1765     }
1766     compilingThrow = prevCompilingThrow;
1767 }
